args: Man, this place hasn't changed at all.
Heeey! You been good while I was out?
It's called a kimono—they wear 'em in\na far-off place called Hinomoto.\nPretty sharp, huh?
You mean...they don't show their\nbelly button in Hinomoto?
Nope! I feel bad depriving the world of it,\nbut these are the sacrifices we make!
It's unusual to get a visit from you out of\nthe blue. To what do we owe the pleasure?
And? I mean, yeah, it's a holiday,\nbut it's not THAT big a deal.
Though I guess humans tend to make\nmore of a fuss about it in some nations.
Sylvans give a quick prayer to the woods,\nfloat some offerings down the river,\neat a meal, and boom! We're done.
Did you really make the trip just for that?
Course I did—so let's get started!
You having fun, Luca? Got any good stories\nfrom the outside world?
Oh, you bet! Plus, there's something I\nwanna do with everybody here.
Yeah! It's this thing where we all go\naround thanking each other.
Some of my buddies are from this country\nout east called Hinomoto, and they've been\nteaching me how they do New Year's there.
Those guys are ALL ABOUT giving thanks.\nThey go nuts for it.
They send postcards, do shrine visits...\nTons of stuff to try and say thanks for last\nyear and wish for good times to come.
And you want to convert us all\nto this Hinomoto way?
Nah, nothing like that; I dig the way\nwe do New Year's, too.
This ain't a competition, and I'm not trying\nto say whose culture does it best.

It's just opened my eyes to just how
important expressing gratitude is. So I
was thinking we could use a bit of that
warm-fuzzy feeling here, too!
It's not about race or where you're from,\nor about specific cultures or traditions.\nIt's just about...us, you know? Everybody.
Guess I can't argue with that.
It's so easy to forget to put your feelings\ninto words and just assume others know\nhow important they are to you.
Yeah, we all take it for granted,\nwhich is why I want a better way.
Most of the time, I'm far away from the\nvillage, so I don't get many opportunities\nto tell you guys how I feel.
But seeing how Hinomotoans do it\nmade me realize I HAD the opportunity—\nI just wasn't making it happen.
So I came back home to spend\nNew Year's with you guys.
Anyway, thanks for everything this year.\nLet's make the next one even better!

Hey, don't mention it! We're all one big
family, after all! Thanks, Luca. I'm glad
we all get to put up with each other for
another year.
And I love how you always tell us\nstories from the outside!
I ALSO love how my mom always makes\nsuper yummy food! Thanks, Mom!
It's my pleasure, sweetheart.\nThank YOU for always cleaning your plate.
(Eh, I guess I can tell him—but ONLY\nbecause it's a special occasion.)

(He deserves to know how much I respect
the way he cares for the people in his life.
Not only that, but he always tries to help
everyone become their best self.)
(Not to mention how much\nhe's taught me...)
(Hope you're ready, Luca, 'cause this\nwon't be no ordinary Sarisse thank-you!)
